<TITLE> Stocks slip slightly </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 6 (bdnews24.com)Stocks fell marginally as the market fluctuated on Wednesday. Dhaka stocks opened strongly but started falling from the midday session as profit-taking pulled down most of the heavyweights. Brokerage house officials said the textile sector and Beximco Group issues rose. "Textile issues continued to rise from [Tuesday] after Delta Spinners surged on the news of the company's bid to raise funds by issuing more shares," an official of Latif Securities told bdnews24.com, asking not to be named. The company is set to raise Tk 45.28 crore for expansion through a repeat IPO and rights shares. It will raise Tk 30 crore only through the IPO, subject to approval of the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC), according to the DSE website. Investors opted for Beximco issues because of its attractive dividend offerings, added the brokerage firm official. The market driversbanksremained more or less steady on Wednesday following gains the previous day. Insurers ended mixed while power sector fell slightly. Mutual funds and non-banking financial institutions also lost. DSE's benchmark general index (DGEN) opened the day with rise of 14 points but ended with a slight loss of 8.32 points or 0.33 percent to 2499.57. The DSI or all share price index ended on 2079.10, slipping 5.03 points or 0.24 percent. The blue-chip DSE-20 crept up 1.88 points or 0.98 percent to finish on 1920.50. Gainers beat losers 119 to 112 while nine issues held steady. Summit Power topped the turnover board with shares worth Tk 693.574 million traded. It shed 0.51 percent to Tk 1347.75. Beximco followed, with a turnover of Tk 439.917 million to gain 3.86 percent on Tk 279.80. State-run Titas Gas ended on Tk 536, falling 2.23 percent. It saw shares worth Tk 321.670 million traded. Z category issue Bextex Ltd saw turnover worth Tk 262.456 million to surge 12.69 percent to close at Tk 42.60. Shinepukur Ceramics, an entity of Beximco Group, saw shares worth Tk 191.164 million traded to end on Tk 107.10, up 5.20 percent. Among the other scrips on the turnover boardBangladesh Online, Beximco Synthetics and Beximco Pharmaceuticalsfinished upbeat. S Alam Cold Rolled Steels and Eastern Housing Ltd fell on selling pressure. Chittagong Stock Exchange Textile, paper and ceramic shares gained the most on the bourse. Turnover amounted to Tk 538.301 million from the trading of 5,582,346 shares. Of the traded issues, 79 advanced, 62 declined with two scrips unchanged. The CSCX or selective categories index shed 7.84 points or 0.14 percent to close at 5246.21. The CASPI or all share price index ended on 8093.72, edging down 1.92 points or 0.02 percent. The CSE-30 blue-chip rose 11.30 points or 0.18 percent to finish at 6286.84. Bextex Ltd topped the turnover board with shares worth Tk 52.36 million changing hands. Titas Gas, Shinepukur Ceramics, Beximco Synthetics and Beximco were the other turnover leaders.
